body:
It means SoftmaxGrad is executed as a single operator as ORT has `a specialized kernel for this op`. This error message can be pretty mis-leading... We have a function body definition for SoftmaxGrad in opset 13 and SoftmaxGrad in opset 12 (or older) doesn't have function body. However, in both cases, the input number is always 2, so I think this error message is not correct. Maybe it should say
```
[Warning] Cannot find function expansion for SoftmaxGrad.
```
@gramalingam, is my understanding correct? I am trying to come up with a fix, so any comments are very welcome.

[Update] The root location of this exception is
```
FunctionImpl::FunctionImpl
    Graph::Resolve
	    Graph::PerformTypeAndShapeInferencing
		    Graph::VerifyNodeAndOpMatch
			    checker::check_node
```
In addition to traditional single operator definition, `SoftmaxGrad` has a composite definition using primitives in opset version 13. When the containing graph specifies opset version to 12, the `checker::check_node` will fail because in opset 12, `Squeeze` has only 1 input but in opset 13, `Squeeze` has 2 inputs. I think it will be better to make ORT throwing this exception earlier with a clear message.

issue.body: This PR proposes a strategy improve the exception mechanism when expanding ONNX's FunctionProto into sub-graph nodes in ORT. It took me a long while to figure out where do we get this error in #9784 since that error was not immediately thrown when seeing a wrong node. That error was thrown when checking the entire graph in the final `Resolve(...)` call after all sub-graph nodes are created.
